%% Journey 2: Process Instance Execution
%% Create a process instance, execute a service task via job worker, complete.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client as Client App
    participant GW as Gateway (REST / gRPC)
    participant Broker as Broker
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant State as State Store
    participant Worker as Job Worker
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch
    participant Operate as Operate

    Client->>GW: Create process instance (REST or gRPC)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCreateProcessInstanceRequest
    Broker->>Engine: PROCESS_INSTANCE_CREATION:CREATE
    Engine->>State: Create instance state
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:ACTIVATED
    Engine->>Log: ELEMENT_ACTIVATING → ELEMENT_ACTIVATED (start event)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine advances through BPMN elements

    Engine->>Log: JOB:CREATED (for service task)
    Engine->>State: Store Job record
    Log->>CExp: Export all events
    CExp->>ES: Index process instance, flow nodes, jobs
    Operate->>ES: Query running instances

    Note over Worker,GW: Job Worker activates & completes job

    Worker->>GW: ActivateJobs (gRPC stream or REST)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerActivateJobsRequest
    Broker->>Engine: JOB_BATCH:ACTIVATE
    Engine->>Log: JOB:ACTIVATED
    Engine-->>Worker: Activated job (via gateway)

    Worker->>Worker: Execute business logic

    Worker->>GW: CompleteJob (with result variables)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCompleteJobRequest
    Broker->>Engine: JOB:COMPLETE
    Engine->>State: Update job + variables
    Engine->>Log: JOB:COMPLETED
    Engine->>Log: VARIABLE:CREATED (result variables)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine continues to next element(s)

    Engine->>Log: ELEMENT_COMPLETING → ELEMENT_COMPLETED (end event)
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:COMPLETED
    Log->>CExp: Export completion events
    CExp->>ES: Update instance state to COMPLETED
